<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12297&amp;p=139863#p139863"><![CDATA[
Something I noticed in Wacky Races (GBC) when I was bored watching videos:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNedYpA7BRg&amp;x-yt-cl=84503534&amp;x-yt-ts=1421914688&amp;feature=player_detailpage#t=1390">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNedYpA ... age#t=1390</a><!-- m --><br /><br />As you can see there's a fog effect where stuff that's far away gets dimmed. Alright, probably some palette stuff... but wait, that thing is eating <em>a lot</em> of palettes, since each sprite gets its own fog level. Hm. (note: in the HUD area it switches sprite palettes on the fly so ignore those... also the constant palette switching mid-screen makes it nearly impossible to check in a debugger)<br /><br />So, stupid question: how many palettes does the GBC have for each layer? Because I completely forgot.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Sun Jan 25, 2015 8:41 am</p><hr />
